{{Expand German|topic=struct|date=November 2011|Bayerische Theatertage}}

The '''Bayerische Theatertage''' (BTT) is a theatre festival in [[Germany]]. It was founded in 1983 by [[August Everding]] and [[Ernst Seiltgen]]<ref>Program Booklet 30. Bayerische Theatertage 2012, p. 13</ref> and is today the largest theater festival in Bavaria. The event series takes place annually at changing venues in Bavaria, the first venue was 1983 Nuremberg. The festival is financially supported by the LfA Förderbank Bayern.

== Weblinks ==
* [http://www.bayerische-theatertage.de/ Official homepage of the festival (content and presentation change annually)]

