'''''Hemidactylus bouvieri''''', also known as '''Bouvier's leaf-toed gecko''' or '''Cape Verde leaf-toed gecko''', is a [[species]] of [[gecko]] in the [[Family (biology)|family]] [[Gekkonidae]].<ref name="RDB">{{NRDB species|genus=Hemidactylus|species=bouvieri|accessdate=3 April 2017}}</ref> The species is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Cape Verde]] Islands and is listed as critically endangered. It has been found on the islands of [[São Vicente, Cape Verde|São Vicente]], [[Santo Antão, Cape Verde|Santo Antão]], [[Santa Luzia, Cape Verde|Santa Luzia]], [[São Nicolau, Cape Verde|São Nicolau]], [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]] and [[Ilhéu Raso]].<ref name=arnold>{{cite journal|url=http://molevol.cmima.csic.es/carranza/pdf/HemidactylusCapeVerde2008.pdf |title= Systematics, biogeography and evolution of the endemic Hemidactylus geckos (Reptilia, Squamata, Gekkonidae) of the Cape Verde Islands: based on morphology and mitochondrial and nuclear DNA sequences|author1=E.N. Arnold|author2=R. Vasconcelos|author3=D.J. Harris|author4=J.A. Mateo|author5=S. Carranza|work=[[Zoologica Scripta]]|volume=37|issue=6|year=2008|pages=619-636}}</ref> 

''H. bouvieri'' was originally described and named by [[Marie Firmin Bocourt]] in 1870. The [[specific name (zoology)|specific name]], ''bouvieri'', is in honor of French zoologist [[Aimé Bouvier]] (died 1919).<ref name="RDB"/><ref>Beolens, Bo; Watkins, Michael; Grayson, Michael (2011). ''The Eponym Dictionary of Reptiles''. Baltimore: Johns Hopkins University Press. xiii + 296 pp. {{ISBN|978-1-4214-0135-5}}. (''Hemidactylus bouvieri'', p. 35).</ref>

==Subspecies==
There are two subspecies which are considered valid.<ref name=arnold/>
*''Hemidactylus bouvieri bouvieri'' {{small|([[Marie Firmin Bocourt|Bocourt]], 1870)}}
*''Hemidactylus bouvieri razoensis'' {{small|[[Hans Jürgen Gruber|Gruber]] & [[Hans Hermann Schleich|Schleich]], 1982}}

The former subspecies ''Hemidactylus bouvieri boavistensis'' is now considered a separate species, ''[[Hemidactylus boavistensis]]''.<ref name=arnold/><ref>{{IUCN | id =18486000/0| taxon = ''Hemidactylus boavistensis''| assessor =R. Vasconcelos| assessment_year =2012 | version = 2018-1| access-date = 2018-10-05}}</ref>

