The '''MR7 road''', also known as the '''Mbandzeni highway''', is a major highway of [[Swaziland]]. Despite being a relatively short road, along with the [[MR3 road|MR3]] and [[MR8 road]]s it is considered to form the "backbone of Swaziland's internal transport system."<ref name="Federation1993">{{cite book|author=International Road Federation|title=World highways|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OmBUAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=22 March 2012|date=1 January 1993|publisher=Route One Publishing}}</ref>It connects the MR3/[[MR16 road]] northeast of [[Siteki]] at {{coord|26|24|1|S|31|51|23|E|}} with [[Mozambique]] near [[Goba, Mozambique|Goba]] at {{coord|26|15|27|S|32|5|2|E|}}.

